ology, film studies, visual studies, and media anthropology, Onscreen/Offscreen rethinks key issues across a number of fields concerned with the semiotic constitution of social life, from the performativity and ontology of images to questions of spectatorship, realism, and presence. In doing so, it offers both a challenge to any approach that would separate image from social context and a new vision for linguistic anthropology beyond the question of "language."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMotion picture industryzIndiazTamil Nadu. 0aMotion pictures and languagezIndiazTamil Nadu. 0aMotion picturesxPolitical aspectszIndiazTamil Nadu. 0aMotion picturesxSemioticszIndiazTamil Nadu. 0aMotion picturesxSocial aspectszIndiazTamil Nadu. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aLinguistics.  aSouth Asia film.  aTamil Nadu.  aTamil.  aanthropology.  acaste in Indian film.  acinema.  agender in Indian film.  aimage.  aontological.  aontology.  aperformativity.  apoliticsIndian film.  asemiotics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781487549060zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487549060zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9